        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>241 W. 34<hi rend="sup">th</hi> St.<lb/>
                New York&#44; 26 Shebat&#44; 5642.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. and dear Sir&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Desirous of bringing thanks<lb/> offerings to our Heavenly Father&#44;<lb/> on the occasion of the <hi rend="underline">Bar Mitzvah</hi><lb/> of my eldest son&#44; Moses Israel&#44; I<lb/> am persuaded that I cannot do<lb/> better than select the Synagogue<lb/> under your ecclesiastical guidance&#44;<lb/> to be one of the recipients of my<lb/> humble tributes.  While regretting<lb/> that the amount is so inadequate<lb/> to the purpose&#44; I would hand you<lb/> here with&#44; twenty five dollars&#44; re&#44;<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>questing of you to obtain of the honora&#44;<lb/>ry officers&#44; its acceptance in favor<lb/> of the treasury&#44; with my best wishes<lb/> for the prosperity of the congregation.<lb/></p>
            <p>And I cannot omit to avail my&#44;<lb/>self of this opportunity to testify<lb/> my acknowledgment of the example<lb/> you set in the admirable stand you<lb/> have taken as one of the champions<lb/> of truth&#44; regardless of its cost to your<lb/> own comfort&#44; and convenience.  A man<lb/> of your faith assuredly derives his<lb/> reward from the satisfaction of<lb/> serving his Maker in doing what he<lb/> deems right&#59; but to know also&#44; that<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>his course elicits the commendation of<lb/> his fellow men&#44; may not be amiss to his<lb/> heart.  It is therefore in the hope that<lb/> you will ascribe my words to their<lb/> right motive&#44; and exonerate me of pre&#44;<lb/>sumption&#44; that I have ventured to ten&#44;<lb/>der you the expression of my esteem<lb/> and regard.<lb/></p>
            <p>That God may bless your endeavors&#44;<lb/> is the prayer of&#44;<lb/>
                Rev. and dear Sir&#44;<lb/>
                Yours truly&#44;<lb/>
                David M. Pizal<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev S. Morais&#44;<lb/>
                Philadelphia.<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
